article.headline: Towson 74, N.C. Central 52
article.story: TOWSON, Md. (AP) -- Rodney Spruill scored a career-high 21 points, Junior Hairston added 15 points and 12 rebounds and Towson pulled away in the second half for a 74-52 victory over North Carolina Central on Tuesday night. Rocky Coleman had 10 points for the Tigers (3-2), eight coming during a game-breaking 18-0 run midway through the second half. Charles Futrell led the Eagles (1-7) with a career-best 20 points. Bryan Ayala scored 13 for North Carolina Central, which lost its second straight and fell to 0-7 on the road in its inaugural Division I season. The Eagles trailed 45-41 with 11:56 left in the second half before Coleman and Hairston combined for 14 of the Tigers' 18 unanswered points for a 63-41 lead. Hairston started and ended the spree with strong inside moves, while Coleman scored on a right-wing 3-pointer, an off-balance leaner and a three-point play. Futrell scored 13 first-half points, but the Eagles committed 14 turnovers and trailed 32-26 after the opening 20 minutes. Towson put together an 11-2 run capped by Coleman's steal and layup for a 27-17 lead with 5:28 remaining in the first half. But North Carolina Central responded by tallying nine unanswered points, cutting the lead to 27-26 on Joshua Worthy's 3-pointer from the left corner.
